Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars in Washington, D.C. He reaffirmed the United States' commitment to an "America First" agenda and emphasized the country's dedication to security and prosperity in the Western Hemisphere. Pence discussed the administration's efforts to address issues in Central America, including illegal immigration, drug trafficking, and gang violence. He also mentioned the Trump administration's new policy towards Cuba and its condemnation of the Maduro regime in Venezuela. Pence highlighted the importance of partnerships and collaboration with countries in the region to achieve shared goals.